claim.claim-text:
1. A method of stimulating neural tissue comprising:
providing a first set of electrodes suitable to stimulate neural tissue;
providing a second set of electrodes suitable to stimulate neural tissue neighboring said first set of stimulating electrodes;
generating a first set of suprathreshold stimulation pulses from said first set of electrodes suitable to induce a first set of percepts; and
generating a second set of suprathreshold stimulation pulses from said second set of electrodes suitable to induce a second set of percepts, wherein said second set of stimulation pulses are phase shifted from said first set of stimulation pulses to avoid electrical field interactions between said first set of percepts and said second set of percepts.

10. A method of stimulating the perception of formed vision comprising:
providing a first set of electrodes suitable to stimulate visual neurons;
providing a second set of electrodes suitable to stimulate visual neurons neighboring said first set of electrodes;
generating a first set of stimulation pulses from said first set of electrodes suitable to stimulate a first set of visual percepts; and
generating a second set of stimulation pulses from said second set of electrodes suitable to stimulate a second set of visual percepts;
wherein said second set of stimulation pulses are phase shifted from said first set of stimulation pulses to avoid electrical field interactions between said first set of visual percepts and said second set of visual percepts.
